Demonstration

Follow the movement slowly and stay within a pain-free range.

Butterfly Stretch (Seated Groin Stretch)

Repetitions not specified
How to do it

Sit on the floor, put the soles of your feet together and let your knees drop out to the sides toward the floor. Keep your back straight as you gently lean forward from the hips. You may press down lightly on your thighs with your elbows to increase the stretch (but do not force the knees down painfully). You should feel a stretch in the inner thighs (groin). The butterfly stretch opens up the hips and stretches the adductors, which can indirectly benefit the knees by improving hip mobility and reducing pull on the knee joint. Hold for 20+ seconds, breathing deeply. This stretch also helps with overall posture and flexibility in the hip region, which contributes to better knee alignment during activities.

Save note
Session tips
  • Move slow. No bouncing.
  • Stop if pain spikes or sharpens.
  • Consistency beats intensity.
